caption: Delicious Japanese, Mexican, and soul fusion food. Wait times can be as long as 30 minutes when it is busy. Enjoy the world music playing in the background while you wait. Limited outdoor seating, and a clean bathroom are available.
Great vibes
Just delicious. Very welcome in Bed-Stuy
Great fast service delicious tea

I’m just annoyed!! Its like Ive lucked out on every single online order this past week. I have no idea what the quality of the food is like because I recess chicken ramen with a whole and and I ordered a vegan ramen. I have dairy allergies so it was super annoying. However the CHOYA!!!! Only reason there’s a star up there, that sake is delicious and made me feel nice.
The ramen was delicious. The perfect way to warm up on a Brooklyn winter evening.

Nice spot...had some hot sake and veggie dumplings and was served outside. Would def visit again...
Great Tacos, great Ramen
WARUDE was fantastic. The food seemed slightly overpriced until I started to dig in. Definitely worth the price!
Love the food the vibe and the music!

I have grown to love it! Great coffee and food, lots of vegan and gluten free options. Dog friendly, when many cafes in the neighborhood do not allow you to walk up to buy a coffee with your dog. Accepts cash or card, which is pretty important in my books. I prefer their tacos over their bowls, try the sweet potato taco, it’s the best!
The customer service is regularly prompt, great ambience, nice staff members. Will come back again when I get in town.
Favorite neighborhood spot. Really great food. Great staff. Great environment.

First of all, the colors are so intriguing. The tastes are so on brand with the presentation. A large bowl with a lot of food and tastes that balances and works well with each other. The drinks were so nice and warm! Not too sweet and tasted exactly to my expectation with your wide choice of leche! I don't like it sweet so order with honey if you need. I was a bit confused whether to go with the Japanese or the Taco options. With the teas it made it easy to decide on the Japanese options. I only give 4 stars because they still use menus wrapped in film instead of an online barcode. It is all self service. And on the sweet and sour was just a bit too saucy for me. But my woman loves it saucy so it worked out!
Loved the food! The dishes had all of my favorite ingredients, great flavor profile, execution and volume! Miss it already

I had the Japanese Curry which reminded me alot of what I ate on my trip to Japan a few years ago! The curry was super flavorful! I also had a chicken tortilla soup which was also delicious. The taco was last on the flavor list but I believe that is because the other two items were sooooo good! Oh and the atmosphere is super cute! Music is always playing and there is seating outside.
Awesome food, nice twist on the 🌮, and friendly staff
Fried chicken 🐔 taco was on point

A fun spot , crispy chicken skin tacos are bomb , chill vibes, with fun music. Outdoor seating available.

You never know what you're going to get with a vegetarian taco, but the yam tacos at Warude are incredible! I really enjoyed the flavor, and the tortillas are sturdy enough that they aren't messy to eat. I also really liked the kale salad (brussels sprouts are a nice touch!). The energy here is just great too. I'll definitely be back!

Incredibly delicious spot in Bed Stuy. Grateful they have outdoor seating. I got the bowl with rice and chicken plus avocado and an organic egg.
Great hidden gem. Nice unique take on tacos. Always have good music playing.

Truly Exceptional!!!♥️♥️♥️ amazingly tasty treats, offering a variety of delicious eats, and seriously yummy beverages, I especially love their matcha, it’s magnificent!🤩😘🤗☝️now they have hats!!! Authentic atmosphere, funky interior and decor (love the upside-down golden arch) great diversity of food options to please picky palates, plus an interesting beer menu! I just wish the prices were a little bit cheaper. The salmon bowl with egg is delicious.
Very good, organic food with some vegan options; the food tastes clean, clear. I hope this makes sense. Owners are very nice and accommodating, and the music is awesome! The neighborhood is good.
Salmon bowl 👍🏾
This place is incredible. We had the warude ramen, yam taco, and special side of the day: mapo tofu. The ambience is awesome!!! Super delicious and very friendly staff. Highly recommend!!!
Good food

Very delicious. I came here with my heart set on ordering tacos from looking at the menu online. Couldn’t resist the Warude Ramen. I’m a seaweed & cabbage junkie.  It’s pay first, but they do accept cards, & you tip immediately. You won’t be disappointed; be generous when you can be.  Very kind staff & the menu really seems to get me. Sometimes you just have a mismatch hankering for nachos AND edamame. I’ll be back.
The miso salmon bowl is so good. The salmon is perfectly seasoned and cooked with deliciously crispy skin. One of the best miso salmons I’ve had!
Great food, the prices are a bit high though. Service is nice, the staff is friendly. Parking can be a little problematic because it's a heavy residential area.

Unexpected Delight❣ Eclectic menu and music makes this a real treat. Grilled salmon taco was EVERYTHING. The vegan ramen left me speechless because I didn't want to stop eating. The "spirits" include varying beers wine & SAKE, coffee and tea. There's leamondes and other bevs in the cooler.
Amazing staff, very unique and delicious fusion cuisine that’s nearly all organic - plus the restaurant is super cool. It’s a win win!
Very cute little place. Delicious food. An amazing combination of authentic ramen and tacos. Family friendly. A cozy neighborhood spot. Super friendly staff.
Really good intimate spot with the really good ramen for a budget.
Sooooo good. Amazing & cozy spot. Food 12/10.
Wonderfully friendly spot perfect fusion of Japanese and American soul food. Unique high quality food and consistent.
New seasonal Ramen is a must try. Perfect portion, right amount of seasoning.
The food is okay and the wait was really long (20-30 minutes). the price also a bit high as well. but love the vibe.
The food is so good I come all the way from manhattan twice a month at least

Love the look of the place and truly hope they succeed. The only problem was that the last time I went the vegetarian dish I ordered with okra had a sauce that was a strange gelatinous texture as if it was not fully cooked. I reheated it at home but it still did not seem right. The portion was a good size but I don’t know how they could serve a sauce like that.
Nice scenery but food is just ok
Awesome place and great food, but the wait is long. One item orders will take about 20 minutes usually.
Great food
Inventive menu and decor, superior service. The place is a joy, and an asset to the neighborhood!
Healthy food
Great little find! Japanese and Mexican food come together in this bed-stuy gem. The food is great value, is high quality and the service is really friendly.

Japanese Plate is very special and tasty!!! especially miso soup, haven’t had miso soup with so many stuffs in it for a loooooooooong time. They have potato seaweed eggplant tofu carrot( which tastes surprisingly good) and a lot of ingredients i didn’t pay attention to lool and the teriyaki chicken is good as well. crispy skin which i love.  large portion like any other US restaurant, but not that salty which is good.  With really nice vibe and fun selection of music (which doesn’t feel like i’m having Japanese plate.)  Glad i walked in :)

This place is fantastic. I was walking by late and hungry, and wandered in. Although the CLOSED sign was on the register, they worked with me to find something I could eat (vegetarian) from among the items the kitchen could still accommodate. I took home a "Japanese bowl" with brown rice, sauteed vegetables, a miso-base soup, and Japanese pickles, all of which were absolutely delicious. Chatted with the owner, who was extremely nice. I can't wait to come back when they're actually open... Give this place your business! Well worth it.

This place has so much vibe. Love it! Most of the food is really fantastic and definitely worth a taste. Staff is always incredibly nice and again...the vibe, the atmosphere, the people... So good! My only beef with this place is the price against the portion size. 3 tacos can easily coast ya close to $13-15, a grain bowl almost $17-20. That not only makes it a really hard place to agree with given the neighborhood and area it's trying to please - sure BedStuy's all the rage, but... No... It seems slightly unfair that tacos and bowls these sizes ring in at those prices. It makes you reconsider options on BedFord Ave and Franklin Ave. Take $1-3 of the prices and this place would be off the hook! No doubt about it!
Very unique menu and aesthetic, great vibe with open air feel. Japanese side of the menu is incredible.
They deliver services are to slow and take forever with they did
Vybz
Wonderful neighbourhood spot for Japanese rice bowls and tacos. Come here on a sunny day when they have the doors open.
Their fried chicken taco is quite delicious just service is sloooooww. I just suggest order ahead and show up in 20mins.
No idea what everyone is praising. Maybe I caught them on a bad day. The tacos took 20 minutes to come out and we're bland all around. Meh.

A gem, brilliant food. Good quality ingredients, with an emphasis on healthy food.  I can recommend everything we had: the fried chicken taco, the teriyaki chicken bowl, the vegetable gyoza, great flavour!
Perfect food and nice Staff paired with a cool location lead to a great experience.
Delicious, high quality food but the wait is very very very long.
Great Teriyaki chicken bowl. Call ahead for it. You won’t be disappointed.
Taste great but small portions
They do Japanese and nachos and tacos really well!
High quality ingredients pay off with really tasty food. Stylish interior and pavement seating are good for watching the cool crowd stroll up and down Tompkins Ave.
The tacos there are delish and the veggie dumplings are as well. Its always clean there and I love how they allow the kids  to scribble on the table covered with paper
Soo good.

Delicious food, and very high-quality ingredients. Everything they use is organic, and the food is always fresh, and just feels like it's made from good stuff. The atmosphere in there is super chill and interesting, the music they play is very nice, and they've got a TV in the background showing sports on occasion. Oh, and not only do they have Japanese dishes, but they also do tacos, which are absolutely bomb. I've been coming here a lot recently, cuz I know I can count on this place for a QUALITY meal. The only downside is that it is indeed a bit expensive, but hey, I can afford it ;)
Good stuff! Healthy.

I want to like this place more but I have some old man complaints about it that kinda temper the experience though. First I'll say, the ingredients taste fresh and everything seems to be done from scratch, big ups. It's the only spot in the neighborhood to get this kind of quality Japanese and fusion grub, which is cool. The vibe of the place though, while bright and sorta fun, feels a bit chaotic and haphazard. The weird tv in the corner above the play area playing like an old dirt bike race or whatever. The dirty menus on the tables. The handwritten signs above the register take a long time to decipher. Nothing's very clear or organized, so it makes you feel like a bit of a dope when you go up and try to figure out what they have, and what you want. I ordered a special from a handwritten sign by the register and they weren't sure if they had the sashimi to produce it. They did in the end, but like, if you've got a sign for a special, you should know that you've got the goods. The tacos came out carefully crafted and tasty but pricey. Almost $6 for a single fish taco? Of which you'd want 3. Kinda wild. The prices feel a bit much. Good hot sauces are available to add if you like. Staff were nice, but again it all feels a bit makeshift, and then you sit down and just stare into the giant coolers that they have full of all their product, right out in the open where you're eating. It's weird. I'll still visit, because I'm nearby and it can scratch an itch. Want to try the bowls, but the vibe is never satisfactory-it feels like a pop up. Or maybe I'm just an old soul 30 year old. Or maybe I just need to take out.
Smallest tacos I have seen. At $6 that feels overpriced.

Luv the food eat here all the time ...nice variety for vegan and non vegan...really cool spot and they have live music sometimes...attentive staff and chill vibe...go in enjoy some food...ots an odd little place VERY BROOKLYN...love it!
The food is always more delicious than the last time. Fresh ingredients & amazing customer service. can't get enough of the eggplant and okra rice bowl.
fold is healthy and delicious
If you’re looking for a flavorless dish; this is the place. We had the salmon and it was bland. Worse dish I’ve ever had while visiting NY!! Not to mention nobody had on gloves.
Chicken Tortilla Soup, Miso Soup, chicken Taco, grilled tuna taco, warm and friendly environment
Great Poke and Japanese Tacos
Don't really get much for your money

I love this place, I’m happy to see them in the neighbourhood. The staff are friendly and knowledgeable. The aesthetic of the space is unpretentious and inviting. Warude offers freshly prepared wholesome foods that are fairly priced. They have real freshly shaven wasabi… mind blown!
Fun place.

As a native new yorker I'm always so skeptical of new restaurants, But Warude was wonderful time . The laid back but exceptional culinary experience makes a warude a place im sure to revisit through the seasons! Besides the food, i love the interior design, Truly something different here at warude 5/5!

I was thinking of giving this a 3 based on prices but that would be unfair since the food is really good. Example I got a shrimp taco for 5.50 and it only had 2 shrimp in it. I really enjoyed eating here but likely will not return unless they moderate their prices.
Over priced, small selection. Food isn't bad, but as others have expressed, I won't go back unless the prices better reflect what you get.
Ok flavor, tiny portions, manhattan prices. Won't revisit.
Nice addition to the neighborhood, but the menu as a whole is quite overpriced for the casual nature of the joint.
Food is great, service is great but the price is absurd for the quantity of food.  Would love to go back once the food is priced accurately

I want to love this place, its service is fast, friendly and full of smiles but like seemingly every other restaurant on our block, it's subpar. The tacos which were very hard to finally get, were lacking in flavor, and in heft yet carried a steep price tag. It could really be something, a sensory contender, there isn't a lot of Japanese food available near by, but the simple offerings feel far too expensive to justify not just going home and slopping some rice and bits together.
Amazing new japanese restaurant with rice bowls, salads, dumplings and tacos. There are great vegetarian options, notably the yam tacos. #vegetarianfriendly
The dumplings are so good! Can’t wait to try the taco!! Welcome to the neighborhood

This tacos and rice-bowl restaurant has a warn handmade garage look with Brooklyn sensitivities. I only had tacos here, which are surprisingly high quality with organic ingredients and first class restaurant quality, made by a serious Japanese chef. Not only the fillings, their tortillas are outstanding as well. Only problem was that the portion was small. Need to order at least 4 to fill 80% of my stomach. But considering the quality, I'm good with it. Alcohol licensing is pending for now.
This place is amazing! Definitely recommend it.
Great atmosphere. Chicken wings were delicious. Haven’t tried the rice bowls, but happy to have this place in the hood. Would love to see more gyoza variety options.

Excited to have this new Japanese flavored restaurant around the corner. I am looking forward to the expansion of the menu, soon there will also be tacos besides ricebowls, soups and salads. I had the miso salmon and really liked the way they cook the brown rice. The flavors altogether were good and it tasted like a wholesome and healthy dish, i was just a bit disappointed what a thin sliver of fish I got for the $15 price tag.  Hopefully once the restaurant is settled and running well the owners might consider giving a bit larger portion of fish for lunch. That would be nice and would make me become a regular.

Today Warude opened up its doors in Bed-Stuy for a soft open. The atmosphere feels perfect for summer and I’m excited for when they begin serving tacos. For now it’s just bowls, soup and salad. I got the Eggplant bowl. It has simple ingredients and a mild flavor. While it isn’t anything to go out of your way for, it’s great to have a low cost healthy option in the neighborhood. Hopefully in the future they’ll put out some shichimi (Japanese chili flakes) or furikake (seasoned seaweed flakes) to boost the flavors a bit.
